// 1. Including Header Files: You can use the #include directive to include standard or user-defined header files in your program. For example:
#include <stdio.h>


// 2. Defining Macros: You can use the #define directive to define a macro, which can be a constant or a macro function. For example:
#define PI 3.14


// 3. Conditional Compilation: You can use directives like #ifdef, #ifndef, #if, #else, #elif, and #endif for conditional compilation. For example, you might have code that should only be compiled for a debug build:
#ifdef DEBUG
    printf("Debugging information...\n");
#endif

// 4. Undefining Macros: If you need to undefine a macro, you can use the #undef directive. For example:
#define PI 3.14
#undef PI